+{"id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.5.1","title":"Zoom: V3 contract, scope, auth model, and service inventory","description":"Define the V3 contract for Zoom. Pin down the exact first-slice service inventory across meetings, webinars, users, recordings, chat or event surfaces where in scope, the auth boundary around accounts and users, OperationInfo risk semantics, and explicit non-goals for the first implementation.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:17:11.953623Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-03-22T03:47:56Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T03:47:56Z","close_reason":"Documented Zoom V3 contract and aligned manifest inventory with actual outbound hosts and implemented operation surface","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"assignee":"RoseAspen","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.5.1","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.11.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:17:11.953623Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.5.1","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.11.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:17:11.953623Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.5.1","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:17:11.953623Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1875,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.5.1","author":"RoseAspen","text":"V3 contract for Zoom:\n\n**Archetype**: Request-response SaaS admin connector. First slice is outbound REST only; no inbound event receiver in this slice.\n**Auth model**: Server-to-Server OAuth using the account-credentials grant with `account_id`, `client_id`, and `client_secret`. Authority is account-level admin context, not per-user delegated OAuth. `user_id` selects which user inside the installed account is targeted.\n**Network**: `api.zoom.us` for REST API calls and `zoom.us/oauth/token` for token acquisition. TLS required. `deny_localhost=true` and `deny_private_ranges=true` remain appropriate.\n\n**Operations (first slice)**:\n| Operation | SafetyTier | RiskLevel | IdempotencyClass | Capability |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| zoom.meetings.list | Safe | Low | None | zoom.meetings.read |\n| zoom.meetings.get | Safe | Low | None | zoom.meetings.read |\n| zoom.meetings.create | Risky | Medium | Strict | zoom.meetings.write |\n| zoom.meetings.update | Risky | Medium | Strict | zoom.meetings.write |\n| zoom.meetings.delete | Dangerous | High | Strict | zoom.meetings.write |\n| zoom.users.list | Safe | Low | None | zoom.users.read |\n| zoom.users.get | Safe | Low | None | zoom.users.read |\n| zoom.recordings.list | Safe | Low | None | zoom.recordings.read |\n| zoom.webinars.list | Safe | Low | None | zoom.webinars.read |\n| zoom.health | Safe | Low | Strict | zoom.users.read |\n\n**Event/webhook stance**: Zoom supports webhook subscriptions, and Server-to-Server OAuth apps can manage them with the account-credentials grant, but this connector's first slice defers webhook subscription management and inbound event delivery. Future event work must request the marketplace event-subscription scopes plus event-specific read scopes.\n\n**Non-goals (first slice)**: No Zoom Chat, Phone, Team Chat, admin/account settings, reports, meeting summaries, registrants/polls/live-stream controls, webinar create/update/delete, recording download/delete/recover, or webhook receiver.\n\n**Truthfulness note**: The official Zoom Meeting API currently supports webinar creation, but the implemented connector slice is list-only for webinars today; the manifest now reflects the actual implemented inventory and the actual outbound hosts (`api.zoom.us` and `zoom.us/oauth/token`).","created_at":"2026-03-22T03:47:56Z"}]}
